            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>JEWISH BIBLE &#38; PUBLISHING HOUSE.<lb/>
                CENTRAL AGENCY&#58;&#45;&#45; 1102 &#38; 1104 Sansom St.&#44; PHILADELPHIA.<lb/></p>
            <p>CANVASSERS WANTED FOR&#58;&#45;&#45;<lb/>
                1. Jewish Family Bible. 4to. 1019 pp.<lb/>
                With Notes and Family Record.<lb/>
                2. Jewish Family Bible. Illustrated ed.<lb/>
                3. Jewish School Bible. 8vo. 1259 pp.<lb/>
                4. The Pentateuch. Hebrew &#38; English.<lb/>
                Five vols. 8vo &#38; 12mo editions<lb/>
                JEWISH EDUCATIONAL COURSE.<lb/>
                1. Primary Catechism for Jewish Children.<lb/>
                2. The Jewish Child&#39;s Catechism of Bible History.<lb/>
                3. The Hebrew Reader.							Pa.<lb/>
                4. The Catechism for Jewish Children. &#40;LEESER&#41;<lb/>
                5. Instruction in the Mosaic Religion. &#40;JOHLSON&#41;<lb/>
                From the MONTREAL Agency.<lb/></p>
            <p>The Rev. S. Mora<lb/>
                546 North Fif<lb/>
                Philadelph</p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>MAY BE HAD AT<lb/>
                THE JEWISH BIBLE &#38; PUBLISHING HOUSE&#44;<lb/>
                Address ABRAHAM DE SOLA&#44; 73 McGill College Ave.&#44; MONTREAL&#44; Can.<lb/>
                E. W. MILLER&#44; 1102 &#38; 1104 Sansom St.&#44; PHILAD&#39;A.<lb/>
                AGENTS			WANTED.<lb/>
                yers&#44; Portuguese Form. 8vo. De Sola&#39;s ed.			The Jewish Faith. by Grace Aguilar. 12 mo.<lb/>
                Do.  &#34; Leeser&#39;s.			The Spirit of Judaism. by the Same. To which is<lb/>
                German Form &#34;			added a collection of her Poetical Writings. 12 mo.<lb/>
                rayer. Portuguese. De Sola&#39;s. 5 or 6 vols. 8 vo.		Meditations &#38; Prayers for the Daughters of<lb/>
                Do. Leeser&#39;s. 6 or 7 vols. 12 mo.			Israel. By Hanna Rothschild. 12 mo.<lb/>
                on the Jewish Religion&#44; with Lectures on			The Ancient Melodies of the Spanish Jews.<lb/>
                ary Subjects.  By Isaac Leeser. 10 vols. 12mo.			by Rev. D. A. De Sola &#38; E. Aguilar.<lb/>
                Sanatory Institutions of the Hebrews. By Abraham de Sola.<lb/>
                Dias&#39; Letters on Judaism &#38; Christianity.<lb/>
                English&#39;s Grounds of Christianity Examined.  Appended.<lb/>
                Dr. Zipser&#39;s &#34;Sermon on the Mount.&#34; The latter also separate.<lb/>
                The Crucifixion &#38; the Jews. by Phillipson.<lb/>
                The Jews &#38; the Inquisition.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>Montreal Novr 30&#47;75.<lb/></p>
            <p>The Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                Philada<lb/>
                Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I have been requested<lb/> by the committee of the Free School of<lb/> the Portuguese Congregation of Montreal<lb/> to write to those gentlemen I addressed<lb/> this &#91;&#63;&#93; last year with the<lb/> view of obtaining a teacher in place<lb/> of Mr. David Levi appointed pastor<lb/> to the Congregation Beth Elohim Charleston&#91;&#63;&#93;.<lb/>  I beg leave therefore to inquire whether<lb/> you can recommend one capable of<lb/> teaching Hebrew and English&#63;  A<lb/> single man is wanted&#44; and the<lb/> appointment would be for one year<lb/> probationary.  The salary is &#36;400 gold<lb/> with residence in school house if<lb/> required&#59; but board could be obtained<lb/> at about &#36;250 per annum.  He could<lb/> increase his income by private teaching<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>and should be able to teach both<lb/> Minhagim.  The appointment will<lb/> probably be made in the early<lb/> part of January.<lb/></p>
            <p>Trusting to be favored<lb/> with a reply at your earliest<lb/> convenience I am&#44; Dear Mr.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours truly<lb/>
                Abraham de Sola<lb/></p>
